These schools are members of the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), and they have over 30,000 pupils across Scotland, and they aim to provide the highest level of services for pupils and their parents.
Independent schools seek to prepare their students for further higher education, their chosen careers, and the status of world citizens.
As part of the education sector that is responsible for developing and implementing individual school curricula, we see that modern languages continue to be a popular and desirable subject for choice in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, "When you talk to a person in a language they understand, you're calling to their mind.
If you speak to him in his native language, you are turning to his heart.
