North Korea says it will not unilaterally disarm without confidence.
North Korea's foreign minister told the United Nations on Saturday that the ongoing sanctions are increasing distrust of the United States and that his country will under no circumstances unilaterally give up its nuclear weapons.
Ri Yong Ho stated at the annual General Assembly that North Korea had taken "essential goodwill measures" last year, such as halting nuclear and missile tests, dismantling a nuclear testing site, and a commitment not to build up nuclear weapons stockpiles and develop nuclear technology.
