Ri referred to a joint statement made by Kim Jong-un and Donald Trump at the first ever summit between the current US president and the North Korean leader, which took place in Singapore on June 12; Kim promised to start a movement toward "denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula", and Trump promised North Korea security guarantees.
North Korea is seeking to officially end the 1950-53 Korean War, but the United States says Pyongyang must first abandon its nuclear weapons.
Washington also opposes calls to ease tough international sanctions against North Korea.
